divs: Sighting DetailsJuly 29, 2004 My family and I were camping on Henvey Island approx. 3 miles duesouth from the town of Key Harbour on Georgian Bay, Ontario Canada. My son wastaking pictures of the sunset he did not see a craft in the sky but he didcapture what appears to be a craft on our digital camera. Attached you will find3 pictures that were taken within a period of two minutes. The last image has awhite self-illuminating triangular object in front of the setting sun. My sonnoticed this image a few minutes after taking the picture when viewing thepictures on the LCD screen on the camera back. These pictures have not beenretouched or affected in any way. I had a professional photographer look at theimage to see if he could explain away what was captured with the camera - lightreflection, spot on lens, bird, etc. - he was not able to explain away whatappears to be some sort of self-illuminated craft.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Key Harbour
This sighting has never been favorited.
Summary: White self-illuminating triangle caught with digit
